Taiwan Stocks: Acer, HTC Corp., Nanya Technology, Hon Hai

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-08-30T02:19:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/taiwan-stocks-acer-htc-corp-nanya-technology-hon-hai.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:01 a.m. local time.  The Taiex Index rose 64.01 points, or 0.8 percent, to
7,642.02, heading for the highest close since Aug. 17.  Exporters:  Acer Inc. (2353)  (2353 TT) led gains in technology
companies after U.S. consumer spending rose more than forecast
and two Greek banks agreed to merge, easing concern  Europe ’s
debt crisis will worsen.  Acer, the world’s fourth-largest computer maker, climbed 7
percent to NT$33, heading for the steepest advance since
November 2008.  HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT),  Asia ’s second-biggest maker
of smartphones, increased 3 percent to NT$791, poised for the
highest close since Aug. 17.  Nanya Technology Corp. (2408)  (2408 TT)
surged by the 7 percent daily limit to NT$4.92.  Hon Hai Precision Industry Co. (2317 TT), the world’s
largest contract manufacturer of electronics, jumped 6.9 percent
to NT$68.60, set for the largest increase since May 2009. Hon
Hai’s operating profit margin widened to 2 percent in the second
quarter, better than the 1.7 percent in the previous three
months, the Taipei-based company said in a statement last night.
Yuanta Securities Co. also lifted the stock’s rating to “buy”
from “hold.”  To contact the reporters on this story:
